# Walter 2.0

A modern CLI command generator with a beautiful TUI interface. Uses local or cloud LLMs to generate shell commands from natural language.

## Features

- **Modern TUI** - Beautiful terminal interface with Rich
- **Multiple Providers** - Ollama (local), Google Gemini, Mistral Codestral
- **Streaming Responses** - See commands as they're generated
- **Command History** - Persistent SQLite-based history
- **Lazy Loading** - Fast startup, providers loaded on demand
- **Interactive Workflow** - Edit, regenerate, refine, copy commands
- **Context Aware** - Knows your OS, current directory, and files
- **Backward Compatible** - Works with v1 configuration files

## Installation

### With pipx (recommended)

```bash
# Basic install (use with Ollama)
pipx install git+https://github.com/NoLilypad/Walter

# With all providers
pipx install "git+https://github.com/NoLilypad/Walter[all]"

# With specific provider
pipx install "git+https://github.com/NoLilypad/Walter[gemini]"
pipx install "git+https://github.com/NoLilypad/Walter[mistral]"
```

### From source

```bash
git clone https://github.com/NoLilypad/Walter.git
cd Walter

# Basic install
pip install -e .

# With all providers
pip install -e ".[all]"
```

### Provider dependencies

Install only what you need:

```bash
# For Ollama (local LLM)
pip install ollama

# For Google Gemini
pip install google-genai

# For Mistral AI
pip install mistralai
```

## Quick Start

```bash
# Generate a command
walter find all python files larger than 1MB

# Open configuration
walter config

# Show help
walter help

# View history
walter history
```

## Usage

1. **Run Walter** with a description of what you want:
   ```bash
   walter compress all images in this folder
   ```

2. **Interact** with the generated command:
   - \`Enter\` - Execute the command
   - \`e\` - Edit command before executing
   - \`r\` - Regenerate command
   - \`c\` - Copy to clipboard
   - \`q\` - Quit
   - \`<text>\` - Refine with additional instructions

## Configuration

Config file is created automatically at \`~/.config/walter/config.yaml\`:

```yaml
# Available providers: ollama, gemini, mistral
provider: ollama
editor: nano
stream: true

ollama:
  model: llama3.2:3b
  temperature: 0.2
  url: http://localhost:11434

gemini:
  model: gemini-2.0-flash
  api_key: "your-api-key"

mistral:
  model: codestral-latest
  api_key: "your-api-key"
```

### Providers Setup

**Ollama (Local)**
1. Install Ollama: https://ollama.ai
2. Pull a model: \`ollama pull llama3.2:3b\`
3. Set \`provider: ollama\` in config

**Google Gemini**
1. Get API key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
2. Set \`provider: gemini\` and add your \`api_key\`

**Mistral AI**
1. Get API key: https://console.mistral.ai/api-keys
2. Set \`provider: mistral\` and add your \`api_key\`

## Custom Prompt

Edit \`~/.config/walter/prompt.md\` to customize the system prompt. Available variables:
- \`{user_prompt}\` - User's request
- \`{os_name}\` - Operating system
- \`{cwd}\` - Current working directory
- \`{files}\` - Files in current directory

## Upgrading from v1

Walter 2.0 is fully backward compatible. Your existing configuration will be automatically migrated on first run. New options (Gemini provider, streaming) will be added while preserving your settings.

## Why Walter?

- **Simple** - One purpose: generate CLI commands
- **Fast** - Lazy loading, minimal dependencies
- **Beautiful** - Modern TUI with Rich
- **Flexible** - Local or cloud LLMs, your choice
- **Practical** - Edit, refine, history - real workflow needs

